In [53]:
n = 10   # Random Sample
p = 0.05 # Failure rate for manufactured item
k = np.arange(0,11)
# For success or failure binomial distribution is used
from scipy.stats import binom
binomial = binom.pmf(k=k, n=n, p=p)
print(binomial)
# For non of them defective
A=binomial[0]
# For one of them defective
B=binomial[1]
# For 2 or few (k<=2)
C=binom.cdf(k=2, n=n, p=p)
# For 3 or more (k>=3) means from 3
D= 1-binom.cdf(k=2, n=n, p=p)
print(A)
print(B)
print(C)
print(D)

# Poisson Distribution
rate = 3
n = np.arange(0,10)
poisson = stats.poisson.pmf(n,rate)
# Sell some cars(means remove the value at 0 index)
A = 1-poisson[0]
# Sell 2 or more but lessthan 5(x>=2 and x<5)
B = poisson[2]+poisson[3]+poisson[4]
print(poisson)
print(A)
print(B)

1Q3C - The poisson distribution function for cumulative probability of cars sold per-week vs number of cars sold per week is :-

4Q) Probability:- p(X-x)=(n!/x!(n-x)!)p^x(1-p)^n-x probability(p) = 86.8%(0.868) Here 1-p = 0.132 n = 3 4A:-Here x=3 =(3!/3!(3-3)!)(0.868)^3(0.132)^3-3 =(0.868)^3 =0.6539(65.39) 4B:-Here x=0 =(3!/0!(3-0)!)(0.868)^0(0.132)^3-0 =(0.132)^3 =0.0023(0.23) 4C:-Here x atleast 2 or more means(probability(x=2)+probability(x=3)) =(3!/2!(3-2)!)(0.868)^2(0.132)^3-2+0.6539 =0.313+0.6539 =0.9524(95.24)</font>

1Q5 :- Real life industry scenario¶

For binomial and poisson distribution¶

A Threadmill Test(TMT) is conducted on 20 individuals in a population. About 35% of individuals performed well and succeded in all stages and are know to have good cardiovascular health. Whereas, remaining members failed to perform well. (Here success and failure are two main entities, as a result we can use binomial distribution for solving any question related to this based on given data).¶

For Poisson distribution :- Average number of patients visiting a hospital on weekends is 25 per hour. Number of patients visit in noon hours. (Here we can use poisson distribution).¶

2 Q3¶

1.Quality :- The data given in the dataset is incomplete as it does not provide complete information regarding the last

Team(Team61). But it is one among the top 10 Highpositioned teams.

2.Quantity :- It has an information about 61 Teams but doesn't mentioned among the members of the team and their

performance.If we know the team members capability in different aspects of game we can analyse and give conclusion about

their position and winning chances of game.

3.Variety :- Information related to wongames, lostgames, Basketgiven, Basketscored were given. Along with this if they had

given the score at each level, in columns we can compare and know at which level they have raised or dropped

their score.

4.Veracity :- Though given dataset is small we cannot accurately predict results as some of the values are not

mentioned(NaN). As a result our assumptions might be true or false.

5.The given data is highly correlated. Tournament, Score,PlayedGames, WonGames, BasketScored are perfectly positively

correlated. TeamLaunch and HighestPositionedHeld are negatively correlated. Overall most the given data is highly

correlated.

6.Skewness :- Almost positive (or) right skewed information. Most of the information for a particular category tend to have

most of its data on left side with its tail on right side.(we conclude this by observing describe table and graphs).

7.Outliers :- As we see a huge difference between Q3 or 75% and maximum value. we could suggest the presence of outliers.

8.The information given consists of data related to very old teams which might not be that much useful for performing and

predicting analysis to present scenario as the performance and capability of old team and newly updated team are different.

9.Though there were no missing and duplicated values, the data contains non-numeric values which does not make any use for

carrying out analysis.

10.Data provides overall team information irrespective of score won by each member of team at different levels of game.
